# Data conventions

## Lazy-load policy (required)

All JSON follows a **fetch-on-demand** graph. Design every new file as part of a lazy-load chain:

| Layer | Load when | Contains |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| Root index | Page init | Country/category ids, names, zone ids — no detail records |
| Country/zone index | User selects country/zone | Beach list with `path` refs only |
| Detail record | User selects item | Full `beach.json`, species card, product |
| Shard file | Slug resolved via index | Up to ~50 species/items per shard |

**Never:**
- Embed full beach, species, or product objects inside index files
- Ship a single JSON file with all countries/beaches/species
- Duplicate the same record in two files — use slug/path refs

**Always:**
- Put `path` or slug on index entries; UI calls `fetchJSON()` when needed
- Keep aggregates precomputed in parent records (e.g. `marine_overview.aggregate_ratings`) — do not compute by fetching all children at runtime

## Explore / beaches

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `countries.json` | Country list + `city_zones[]` with ids |
| `{country}/country.json` | Ocean overview, coast guide, `marine_overview` |
| `{country}/search-index.json` | Country trie source: names, aliases, `search_tags` |
| `{city_zone}/city-beaches.json` | Beach index: `{ id, name, tags, path }` |
| `{beach}/beach.json` | Full record: `live_rating`, `live_rating.tide.{next_high,next_low}`, `ecosystem`, `map_link` |

Use kebab-case slugs for ids. `live_rating` scores are 0–10 integers where numeric.

### `marine_overview` (in country.json)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| `known_beach_count` | number | Matches search-index when beaches exist |
| `aggregate_ratings` | object \| null | `swim`, `wave`, `snorkeling`, `scuba`, `water_quality`, `surfing` — 0–10 |
| `aggregate_scope` | string | e.g. `leeward_coast` — which beaches were averaged (exclude non-visitor coasts) |
| `aggregate_notes` | string | Explains scope; shown on country card |
| `ocean_character` | string | Short summary for country card |
| `best_seasons` | string[] | Visiting seasons |
| `species` | string[] | Slug refs only — resolve via marine-life paths |

## Education / species (preferred)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `species/index.json` | Shard registry for hub nav (`id`, `path`, `count`) — no full records |
| `species/search-index.json` | Trie source: slug, names, tags, `shard` — no full records |
| `species/shards/{prefix}.json` | Up to ~50 full records; `prefix` = first 2 letters of slug |

**Shard rule:** `shardId = slug.replace(/[^a-z0-9]/g,"").slice(0,2)` — UI derives shard from slug (no index fetch to open a card).

Cross-ref beaches/countries → species by **slug only**. Overlay/hub fetch one shard file on demand.

Legacy `marine-life/{animals\|plants}/{slug}.json` remains a fallback until migrated.

## Eco Shop

`data/eco_shop/{category}/catalog.json` — product index with refs; fetch item detail only when opened.

Do not hardcode product or beach counts — read the index JSON.
